rComments: This was my absolute favorite class last semester...and I'm an English major.  Professor Roseman is very entertaining and informative; he has a way of delivering info that makes it stick.  If you go to lecture, you'll do fine.  I didn't even do any of the readings, and I still got a B+.

Nothing from the reading is on the tests except quiz questions, so memorize those.  The tests are pretty hard but if you go to class you will be fine.  pay attention when he talks about examples in class because a ton of them were on the tests.  hard class for a gen ed, but possible to get an A
his tests were impossible and he never knew what to say.

The class started slow, but became more interesting. He said he would curve the grades, but he didn't. He wont return emails about the class, so I emailed a TA who never responded.  People posted on compass about how he didn't curve/round-he just removed the disucssion page from our site.  Overall, it was an ok class- just dont expect to get an A.

good teacher, knows his anthro, but too hard for a 100 level class. the tests are ambiguous. the online quizzes are easy...i never read the books and since they arent timed i looked up all the answers and got 100% on all the tests. the prof means well though, i felt bad for him sometimes...haha

extroadinarily nice guy. More than happy to help you understand the material, and encourages visits during office hours. Review sheets are detailed and comprehensive, and the online quizzes are a breeze. Not the easiest life sciences course out there, but very interesting

The Chuckster is a pretty food professor for his first year of teaching.  He knows what hes talking about and you can tell he likes it a lot.  However, the class is boring and more difficult than an introductory, gen-ed class should be.  The online quizzes are easy, but the tests can be confusing if he makes one of the answers none of the above.

for an introductory anth class, this class is way too hard. His tests usually have the none of the above answeres and all answers are very similar except for like one word. Not necessarily difficult subject, but his tests suck and for the level class that it is, its way too hard. dont take it if you can get another gen ed. big mistake.
The lectures are usually pretty boring, but he's a good teacher and knows anthro.  the online quizzes aren't hard as long as you do the reading.
